==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Transfigure
<hw>Trans*fig"ure</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Transfigured</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Transfiguring</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>transfigurer</ets>, L. <ets>transfigurare</ets>,
<ets>transfiguratum</ets>; <ets>trans</ets> across, over +
<ets>figurare</ets> to form, shape. See <er>Figure</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To change the outward form or
appearance of; to metamorphose; to transform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Especially, to change to something exalted and
glorious; to give an ideal form to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>[Jesus] was <qex>transfigured</qex> before them; and his face did
shine as the sun, and his raiment was white as the light.</q>
<rj><qau>Matt. xvii. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Transfix</ent>⟦br⟧
